# Common Coding Style

## Naming
- Variables/Functions: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Classes/Types: PascalCase
- Files: kebab-case
- Booleans: is/has/can/should prefix

## Code Organization
- One class/component per file
- Group imports: external → internal → relative
- Public methods before private
- Max function: 30-50 lines, max file: 300-500 lines

## Principles
- Single Responsibility (SRP)
- DRY, KISS, early return
- Avoid magic numbers (use constants)

## Error Handling
- Never swallow exceptions
- Log with context and stack trace
- Fail fast, fail loud

## Logging
- Use appropriate levels (debug/info/warn/error)
- Include context (IDs, request info)
- Never log sensitive data
